Sentencas: Planar solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) are composites consisting of porous and dense functional layers as electrodes and electrolytes, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of alumina on the curvature, Young's modulus, thermal expansion coefficient and residual stress of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Because of the thermo-elastic mismatch between the individual layers, residual stresses develop during manufacturing and cause unconstrained cells to warp.
Titulo: Effect of alumina on the curvature, Young's modulus, thermal expansion coefficient and residual stress of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The addition of alumina decreases the thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of the NiO and yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) anode-support material.
Titulo: Effect of alumina on the curvature, Young's modulus, thermal expansion coefficient and residual stress of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Correspondingly, the lower TECs have flattened the half cells during fabrication.
Titulo: Effect of alumina on the curvature, Young's modulus, thermal expansion coefficient and residual stress of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the residual stress at room temperature (RT) for samples with more than 4 wt% alumina is only 20% of the residual stress of the samples without alumina, at approximately 100 MPa.
Titulo: Effect of alumina on the curvature, Young's modulus, thermal expansion coefficient and residual stress of planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of Al(2)O(3) on the curvature, Young's modulus, TEC and residual stress of the SOFC with (NiO-YSZ)(1-x)(Al(2)O(3))(x) (x = 1-5 wt%) anode support are discussed in this work.
